node.title: A Refugee Crisis Runs Into a Housing Crisis
node.description: Thousands of Afghan refugees are being released from military bases to U.S. cities to rebuild their lives. Settling them into homes amid a rental shortage is proving to be a challenge.

node.title: The Nobel Peace Prize That Paved the Way for War
node.description: This is the story behind how Ethiopia’s prime minister, Abiy Ahmed, won a Nobel Prize for making peace with his country’s longtime enemy — and then used the alliance to plan a war.

node.title: Putin and Xi Show United Front Amid Rising Tensions With U.S.
node.description: President Vladimir V. Putin and President Xi Jinping of China, meeting in a video summit, sought mutual support in their conflicts with the West over Ukraine, Taiwan and other issues.

node.title: Mitch McConnell Hated Donald Trump More than He Loved Being Majority Leader
node.description: In this daily series, Newsweek explores the steps that led to the January 6 Capitol Riot.

node.title: How NASA Probe Beat the Heat to Become First Spacecraft to Touch the Sun

node.title: Geraldo Rivera Condemns Sean Hannity Over Jan. 6 Text: 'Remember That Concern You Had'

node.title: Grandmother accused of killing daughter, other woman during street fight awaits her fate

node.title: Pro sports taking big COVID hit as Omicron variant spreads rapidly

node.title: Hong Kong Shopping Mall Fire Leaves Over 300 Trapped on Roof

node.title: NASA's Parker probe 'touches' the Sun by crossing the corona boundary

node.title: 'He picked up the basket and threw it with the baby still in it': Inquest hears of alleged past abuse

node.title: 'Most serious, 10 out of 10' software risk that is threatening global online security

node.title: He Was Convicted of Raping Alice Sebold. Then the Case Unraveled.

node.title: Fourth Stimulus Check Update: Some Americans Are Receiving $1,500 Payments or More

node.title: Torrance Mall Shooting Sees Three Teens Gunned Down in California

node.title: New Zealand producers' effort to trademark words 'Manuka honey' rejected by UK

node.title: 'There's a buzz in the air' as Aucklanders roam free today

node.title: Grieving relatives left furious after St Basil's managers refuse to speak at inquest into deadly outbreak

node.title: Late Night Praises Fox News Hosts for Their Acting Skills

node.title: China critic forms new political party with young, diverse candidates ahead of federal election
